.TH CHECKREADME 1 "March 2026" "AutoReadme" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
checkreadme \- Validate README.md file table against actual directory contents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B checkreadme
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B checkreadme
validates that the file table in README.md accurately reflects the current directory contents. It checks for:
.IP \(bu 2
Files that exist but are not listed in README.md
.IP \(bu 2
Files listed in README.md but not found in directory
.IP \(bu 2
Empty descriptions in the table
.IP \(bu 2
Proper table formatting
.PP
Files marked with '!' prefix (older/removed files) are allowed to be missing.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
README.md table is valid
.TP
.B 1
Issues found in README.md table
.SH OUTPUT
Prints validation results:
.IP \(bu 2
"✅ README.md file table is valid." on success
.IP \(bu 2
Detailed error messages for each issue found
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Validate current README.md:
.B checkreadme
.SH FILES
.TP
.B README.md
The README file to validate
.TP
.B ignore_list.txt
Local ignore list file
.TP
.B ~/.config/autoreadme/ignore_list.txt
User-specific ignore list
.TP
.B .gitignore
Git ignore rules are respected
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR generate_table (1),
.BR merge_table (1),
.BR autoreadme (1)
.SH AUTHOR
AutoReadme project